<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,799,824]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[668,793,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradleyi">
<emphasis box="[668,793,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. bradleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the head longer than wide; the mandible with the two upper teeth wider and longer than the others; the eye large; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle acute; the pronotal disc with a posterior pronotal sulcus; and the mesotibia not spinose, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[1164,1289,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradleyi">
<emphasis box="[1164,1289,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. bradleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the head long; the mandible wide, slightly angled, and step-shaped with five distal teeth,; the eye small; the frontal angle of the ocellae forming a right angle; the pronotal disc without a posterior pronotal sulcus; and the mesotibia spinose.
</paragraph>
